properties.abstract: Lush green flower meadows, fascinating fauna, an emerald green mountain lake with temperatures as high as 23 degrees and a fantastic view of the mountains – you'll find it all in the village of Lungern.
properties.description:
One of the nicest bicycle trails is the one leading around the lake; it’s both easy and exciting. You start in Obsee, right next to the «Lungern-Turren-Bahn» station. This is also where you’ll find the Brünig Indoor shooting center. In June and July you can see more than 100 types of butterflies in the nature paradise of Brünig-West.

After you pass Kaiserstuhl and Bürglen, you’ll see the Dundelsbach waterfall. The two-level fall is definitely worth a closer look. It’s under national protection.
